<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id9029995a-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s2904"><num value="2904">§ 2904.</num><heading> Functions of Commission</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id9029995b-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s2904/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> Promotion of scholarly, cultural, and artistic activities; grants</heading><chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Commission is authorized to—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id9029995c-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s2904/a/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> develop and carry out programs at public or private institutions for the promotion of scholarly, cultural, and artistic activities in Japan and the United States consistent with the provisions of <ref href="/us/usc/t22/s2902/b">section 2902(b) of this title</ref>; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id9029995d-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s2904/a/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> make grants to carry out such programs.</content>
</paragraph>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id9029995e-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s2904/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Annual report</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Commission shall submit to the President and to the Congress an annual report of its activities under this chapter together with such recommendations as the Commission determines appropriate.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id9029995f-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">(<ref href="/us/pl/94/118/s5">Pub. L. 94–118, § 5</ref>, <date date="1975-10-20">Oct. 20, 1975</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/89/605">89 Stat. 605</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
